---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Citations - ANT 104">
  <header
    class="relative overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-paper via-white to-paper py-6 md:py-8"
  >
    <div
      class="pointer-events-none absolute top-0 left-0 w-64 h-64 bg-sage/5 rounded-full -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2"
    >
    </div>
    <div
      class="pointer-events-none absolute bottom-0 right-0 w-96 h-96 bg-terracotta/5 rounded-full translate-x-1/2 translate-y-1/2"
    >
    </div>
    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 text-center">
      <span
        class="inline-block px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-terracotta bg-terracotta/10 rounded-full mb-2"
        >References</span
      >
      <h1
        class="whitespace-nowrap text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-ink mb-2 leading-tight"
      >
        Citations & References
      </h1>
    </div>
  </header>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <section class="space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink">Works Cited</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-ink/85 leading-relaxed">
        <p class="pl-8 -indent-8 mb-4">
          Axelsson, E., et al. "The Genomic Signature of Dog Domestication Reveals Adaptation to a Starch-Rich Diet." <em>Nature</em>, vol. 495, 2013, pp. 360–364. https://doi.org/10.1038/nature11837.
        </p>
        <p class="pl-8 -indent-8 mb-4">
          Bergström, Anders, et al. "Origins and Genetic Legacy of Prehistoric Dogs." <em>Science</em>, vol. 370, no. 6516, 2020, pp. 557-564. https://doi.org/10.1126/science.aba9572.
        </p>
        <p class="pl-8 -indent-8 mb-4">
          Freedman, A. H., et al. "Genome Sequencing Highlights the Dynamic Early History of Dogs." <em>PLOS Genetics</em>, vol. 10, no. 1, 2014, p. e1004016. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pgen.1004016.
        </p>
        <p class="pl-8 -indent-8 mb-4">
          Janssens, Luc, et al. "A New Look at an Old Dog: Bonn-Oberkassel Reconsidered." <em>Journal of Archaeological Science</em>, vol. 92, 2018, pp. 126-138. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jas.2018.01.004.
        </p>
        <p class="pl-8 -indent-8 mb-4">
          Larson, G., and D. G. Bradley. "How Much Is That in Dog Years? The Advent of Canine Population Genomics." <em>PLOS Genetics</em>, vol. 10, no. 1, 2014, p. e1004093. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pgen.1004093.
        </p>
        <p class="pl-8 -indent-8 mb-4">
          Ollivier, Morgane, et al. "Dogs Accompanied Humans During the Neolithic Expansion into Europe." <em>Biology Letters</em>, vol. 14, no. 10, 2018, p. 20180286. https://doi.org/10.1098/rsbl.2018.0286.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12 space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink">Image Citations</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-ink/85 leading-relaxed">
        <p class="pl-8 -indent-8 mb-4">
          Image 1, Home: "Paleolithic Humans Domesticate Dogs and Spread Them Across Eurasia." <em>ChosunBiz</em>, 26 Mar. 2026, https://biz.chosun.com/en/en-science/2026/03/26/GGMXECAQP5BEVEHXTXXSYTOYIQ/.
        </p>
        <p class="pl-8 -indent-8 mb-4">
          Image 2, Genetic Diet: Figure 4 from Bergström, Anders, et al. "Origins and Genetic Legacy of Prehistoric Dogs." <em>Science</em>, vol. 370, 2020, pp. 557-564. <em>Science</em>, https://www.science.org/doi/10.1126/science.aba9572.
        </p>
        <p class="pl-8 -indent-8 mb-4">
          Image 3, Social Bonds: Bonn-Oberkassel Canine Remains Visual Record from Janssens, Luc, et al. "A New Look at an Old Dog: Bonn-Oberkassel Reconsidered." <em>Journal of Archaeological Science</em>, vol. 92, 2018, pp. 126-138. <em>ScienceDirect</em>, https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0305440318300049?via%3Dihub.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-12 space-y-4">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-ink">AI Transparency</h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-ink/85 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          AI was used alongside my computer science software development major skills for the technical aspect of this project. Kimi.ai was used to assist in the formatting of the initial annotated bibliography and helped with search terms for researching. Step 3.7-flash and eventually Claude Haiku was used as a coding assistant to write the Astro and Tailwind CSS framework, format the MLA citations, and help synthesize and edit the provided academic quotes into the final readable web copy. All core research directions, source selections, and the overarching thesis framework were independently developed by me, Hammy S.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
